{"id":7514,"date":"2018-08-23T18:04:15","date_gmt":"2018-08-23T18:04:15","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/c4c.greasbygraphics.com\/?page_id=7514"},"modified":"2020-06-05T17:51:44","modified_gmt":"2020-06-05T17:51:44","slug":"dunkirk","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/about-us\/what-we-do\/dunkirk\/","title":{"rendered":"Dunkirk"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Since April 2017, when the camp at Dunkirk burnt down, there have been refugees camping in the woods and fields in this area. They are mainly either Kurdish or Afghan and include many families with small children. Care4Calais visits sites here twice a week to deliver direct aid, charge mobile phones, bring hot tea, food packs and firewood, and to engage in social activities with the refugees.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-7517\" src=\"http:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk2-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"485\" height=\"323\" srcset=\"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk2-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk2-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk2-600x400.jpg 600w, https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk2-100x67.jpg 100w, https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk2.jpg 810w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 485px) 100vw, 485px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>There have been various initiatives by the French authorities to bus people out to French welcome centres, but despite this people either return or new people arrive, and the problem in Dunkirk continues.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-7516\" src=\"http:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk-200x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"484\" height=\"726\" srcset=\"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk-200x300.jpg 200w, https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk-100x150.jpg 100w, https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2018\/08\/Dunkirk.jpg 540w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 484px) 100vw, 484px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Since April 2017, when the camp at Dunkirk burnt down, there have been refugees camping in the woods and fields in this area. They are mainly either Kurdish or Afghan and include many families with small children. Care4Calais visits sites here twice a week to deliver direct aid, charge mobile phones, bring hot tea, food packs and firewood, and to engage in social activities with the refugees. &nbsp; &nbsp; There have been various initiatives by the French authorities to bus people out to French welcome centres, but despite this people either return or new people arrive, and the problem in Dunkirk continues. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":7588,"parent":7044,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/7514"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=7514"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/7514\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":21300,"href":"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/7514\/revisions\/21300"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/care4calais.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/7044"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\